.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
See
.Xr environ 7
for descriptions of the following environment variables that affect the
execution of
.Nm :
.Ev LANG ,
.Ev LC_ALL ,
.Ev LC_CTYPE ,
.Ev LC_MESSAGES ,
.Ev LC_TIME ,
and
.Ev NLSPATH .
.Bl -tag -width Ev
.It Ev COLUMNS
Override the system-selected horizontal screen size, used to determine the
number of text columns to display.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Pa
.It Pa /dev/pts/* , Pa /dev/term/*
terminal
.Pq Dq tty
character devices
.It Pa /etc/passwd
UID information supplier
.It Pa /proc/*
process control files
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The following exit values are returned:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Sy 0
Successful completion.
.It Sy >0
An error occurred.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Sy Example 1
Using
.Nm
Command
.Pp
The command:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
example% ps -o user,pid,ppid=MOM -o args
.Ed
.Pp
writes the following in the POSIX locale:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
 USER  PID   MOM   COMMAND
helene  34    12   ps -o uid,pid,ppid=MOM -o args
.Ed
.Pp
The contents of the
.Sy COMMAND
field need not be the same due to possible truncation.
