.Sh NOTES
Things can change while
.Nm
is running.
The snapshot it gives is true only for a split-second, and it might not be
accurate by the time you see it.
Some data printed for defunct processes is irrelevant.
.Pp
If no options to select processes are specified,
.Nm
reports all processes associated with the controlling terminal.
If there is no controlling terminal, there is no report other than the header.
.Pp
.Nm
.Fl eF
or
.Nm
.Fl o Ar stime
might not report the actual start of a tty login session, but rather an earlier
time, when a getty was last respawned on the tty line.
.Pp
.Nm
is CSI-enabled except for login names
.Pq usernames .
